As for languages: a limit by what season you are?? You tell me a young person can not learn as well, and in most cases better, than an older one? The fact that it took so long was just an irritant, nothing more. In most other RPGs do you spend hours learning a language? No you put some skill points in to it &amp; say it happened during &quot;Down Time&quot;. That is not available in EQ so should we be punished by having to sit for hours to learn a few points? No. <br>
And don't tell me that this is an imersive game &amp; you have to sit through everything! Can you tell me when the last time your &quot;Got to go potty&quot; bar was full so you had to run to Thurgadin to use the bathroom?! . . . . . I did not think so.<br>
Role-playing is not a set of rules, it is a choice, there will always be people who choose not to, you can not stop them, so why try, ignore them &amp; move on. I have played Role Playing Games for 21 years, in just about every rule set I could find, I do not want SOE or VI to tell me how to RP, I and all of you can figure it out all by our little selves.<br>
I have said my peace, Good Journey to all.<br>
<br>
<br>
Monoglory Quayein<br>
High Elven Priestess of The Mother of ALL, Tunare.<br>
Healer of the Council of Mithril Dreams.<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=393409">Behold my Faith</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vuxxfv>Vuxxfv</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.indigovoid.net/images/roster/7_icon" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/24/03 7:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3840.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/jpariseau4/Vuxx2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My peace</span><hr size=1> If your &quot;Uncle&quot; is truly good, then let me watch him march into Felwithe unharmed and I will believe you. The guards there are also followers of the &quot;Mother of All&quot; and yet they do not hesitate for a moment to raise their blades against anyone who is of an evil nature...regardless of what &quot;potential good&quot; they have in them. Plus, if I took a trip to see Tunare herself for some light conversation, I guarantee I would not finish my first sentence before my dead corpse lay at her feet.<br>
<br>
As for roleplaying being a choice and simply avoiding those that do not, that has become impossible. Sadly, there are few roleplayers left on this server(all due respect to the great roleplayers that I HAVE met). You can not visit the Plane of Knowledge or the Bazaar without hearing someone named &quot;Iamcute Givemestuff&quot; shouting for KEI or SoW or just some money to get started. I miss the days when shout and auction were limited. It was a peaceful environment where we could really roleplay with each other. <br>
<br>
With the old ruleset, those who did not wish to roleplay learned either to adapt and deal with the bit of roleplaying that was enforced by the ruleset or they left for blue servers. It was nice to honestly be able to tell a high elf, &quot;I am sorry, I cannot give you clarity since you are a follower of the light&quot;, sneer at them and take off. People did not randomly ask for buffs since you could not &quot;randomly&quot; buff people. And finding groups was not that hard. You just had to grin and bear the fact that you would actually have to send a tell to someone and ask their alignment and then ask if they could use a hunting partner. If they were of incompatible alignment, then you found someone with whom you could roleplay an adversity...it was fun back then.<br>
<br>
As for the number of characters, I am SO glad they did not change that!! The number of twinks would have been unbearable. It was so wonderful to play in a world where there were no level 1 rogues with jboots or level 5 shadowknights with planar armor. This rule I think was critical. If they had changed that, then we would have taken this downward spiral much sooner.<br>
<br>
I have stopped by some blue servers from time to time to see how they compare and honestly, some blue servers are not even as bad as some of the crap that I see and hear in the Plane of Knowledge. Far less shouts for buffs...less shouts period and not as many ridiculous names made it actually bearable to sit up there for a few moments without losing my mind completely.<br>
<br>
This is a Roleplay Preferred server and as mentioned before that means it is for those who &quot;prefer&quot; to roleplay, not that roleplaying is an option. If you have no intention of roleplaying than scroll down the list of servers and choose ANY of the other servers to go to. If you are not a roleplayer, then you clicked the wrong damn button when you signed up. You do not need to be as hardcore as, say Shintou, but at least try to stay somewhat in character at least SOME of the time.<br>
<br>
It is sad and pathetic what this server has become. I stay because I have many friends here that are fun to roleplay and hunt with....when we can get away from the d00ds that swarm everywhere. I do miss those days before May 8th, when this server truly lived up to its name.<br>
<br>
